===Interjection===
{{en-interj}}

# {{senseid|en|interjection}} {{lb|en|colloquial}} {{n-g|A [[holophrastic]] expression used to dismiss something that the speaker doesn't care about, doesn't think important, or doesn't want to consider or discuss any further.}}
#: {{ux|en|So you don't like Mrs Jones. '''Whatever'''. What's that got to do with my question?}}
#: {{ux|en|I wonder which I'm supposed to take ... '''whatever''', I'll just pick any one.}}
#: {{ux|en|Go brush your teeth. – '''Whatever'''!}}

====Usage notes====
* May appear rude or discourteous. Can be used to end an argument without conceding the point, implying that the issue is not worth discussing or indicating a general sense of apathy toward the subject.

